	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi></p>
				<p>To my friend&#44; etc&#44; <addressee>Rev. Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I&#44; too&#44; request that you grant the wish of<lb/> my dear friend&#44; <persName>Finkelstein</persName>&#44; which is also my<lb/> wish.  Don&#39;t let it surprise you that I haven&#39;t<lb/> written to you for <del>some</del> long&#44; as is proper between two<lb/> good friends.  The reason is that I had no peace<lb/> from a man who hates me and who is my bitter<lb/> enemy&#44; <persName>Zoi</persName>&#44; a scribe from <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; who came here<lb/> last winter and accused me of very ugly doings<lb/> in <placeName>N. Y.</placeName>  He went from house to house slaughter&#45;<lb/>ing fowl&#44; and&#44; with a smooth tongue&#44; he aroused<lb/> the entire community against me.  A long time<lb/> posted until his lies <del>it became known</del> were refuted<lb/> from <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; and all the honor I received<lb/> there became known.  Then the dispute quieted<lb/> down&#44; but two enemies remained&#44; and&#44;<lb/> after the <date>Passover</date>&#44; when he departed&#44; I began<lb/> to open my eyes.  But now recently&#44; the two<lb/> enemies once more aroused themselves&#44; <del>an</del><lb/> since this man is coming here.  For myself&#44; I<lb/> have always loved peace and have always kept<lb/> away from dispute.  Therefore&#44; I ask with<lb/> my very soul that you be good enough to</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>announce in your newspaper to all the<lb/> Jews that there is a certain man&#44; a rabbi<lb/> a chazan and a schochet&#44; a reader of the<lb/> Torah&#44; a Mohel&#44; and a shofar blower&#44; and<lb/> my view is that you should not reveal my<lb/> name&#44; for&#44; as the saying goes&#44; &#34;One should not<lb/> throw away muddy water&#44; unless he has<lb/> clean water&#44;&#34; and for a wise man like you&#44;<lb/> this List is sufficient.  I am waiting<lb/> expectantly for your reply.  Whatever the<lb/> cost of the printing will be&#44; please let me<lb/> know and I will pay <del>whatever</del> as well as I<lb/> can.  I also have shofars &#40;<add>&#63;</add>&#41;<lb/> to sell which I am having made by a skilled workman&#44;<lb/><persName> Moses Katzenellenbogen</persName>.</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Moses Bogen</persName>.</p>
